* [BJ Fogg's Behavior Model](http://www.behaviormodel.org/) by Dr. BJ Fogg, founder of the Persuasive Technology Lab at Stanford University
* [Flow](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flow_(psychology)) - concept introduced by Dr. Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi, former head of the department of psychology at the University of Chicago. More information in the book ["Flow: The Psychology of Optimal Experience"](http://www.amazon.com/Flow-The-Psychology-Optimal-Experience/dp/0061339202)
* [Deliberate Practice](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deliberate_practice#Deliberate_practice) - concept introduced by Dr. K. Anders Ericsson, Professor of Psychology at Florida State University. More information in the book ["Talent Is Overrated: What Really Separates World-Class Performers from Everybody Else"](http://www.amazon.com/Talent-Overrated-World-Class-Performers-EverybodyElse/dp/1591842948)
* [The Surprising Science of Motivation](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rrkrvAUbU9Y) - TED Talk by Daniel Pink (Author of [Drive](http://www.danpink.com/drive))

* [Are Games Better Than Life?](http://www.ted.com/talks/david_perry_on_videogames.html)- TED Talk by David Perry

* [Ways that games reward the brain]( http://www.ted.com/talks/tom_chatfield_7_ways_games_reward_the_brain.html)- TED Talk by Tom Chatfield, Chatfield looks into the ways that games engage the brain through intrinsic reward systems within the brain.
